Interface Concept.Super<O,J,D extends Concept<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the ontology.
    J - the type of Ground and EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of Concept descriptor instantiated during buildSuperConcept() ()} through getNewSuperConcept(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, Concept<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConceptExpression.Super<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FullConceptDescriptor, HierarchicalConceptDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    Concept<O,J>

    public static interface Concept.Super<O,J,D extends Concept<O,J>>
extends Concept<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a Concept to have the Concept.Super expression.

    • Method Detail

      • readExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> readExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        readExpressionAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Axiom.EntitySet during the reading. Note that the elements of the returned list, may not have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • buildSuperConcept

        default java.util.Set<D> buildSuperConcept()
        Create an Axiom.Descriptor set where each element represents the super classes of this Concept. Each of those Concepts are instantiated through the method getNewSuperConcept(Object, Object); this is called for all getSuperConcept().
        Returns:
        the set of Concepts that describes the super entities of this described ontological class.

      • getNewSuperConcept

        D getNewSuperConcept(J instance,
                     O ontology)
        This method is called by buildSuperConcept() and its purpose is to instantiate a new Concept to represent an super class of this Concept Descriptor.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance to ground the new Concept.
        ontology - the ontology in which ground the new Concept.
        Returns:
        a new Axiom.Descriptor for all the super classes of this descriptor.

      • synchroniseSuperConceptToExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseSuperConceptToExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet) with querySuperConcept() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getSuperConcept(). This should be done by Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the super classes of an OWL class.

      • synchroniseSuperConceptFromExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseSuperConceptFromExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) with querySuperConcept() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getSuperConcept() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the super classes of an OWL class with this structure.
